President Joe Biden has appointed Erika L. Moritsugu as Deputy Assistant to the President and Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) Senior Liaison. Moritsugu, currently the Vice President at National Partnership for Women & Families, has a background in fighting for social justice and community empowerment. She has previously served in various roles in the federal government, including Assistant Secretary for Congressional and Intergovernmental Relations at the Department of Housing and Urban Development under the Obama Administration. Moritsugu has also worked in organizations such as the Anti-Defamation League and has extensive experience on Capitol Hill. She holds degrees from Brandeis University, the College of William and Mary, and George Washington Law School. Moritsugu, who was born in California and raised in Hawai'i, currently lives on Capitol Hill with her husband, two children, and two cats.